Preconditions:
- The input array `nums` must have a length greater than or equal to 3.
- The elements of the input array `nums` must be non-negative integers.
- The value of `k` must be a non-negative integer.

Postconditions:
- The output must be an integer representing the minimum number of increment operations needed to make the input array `nums` beautiful.
- The input array `nums` must remain unchanged after the method is executed.
- The maximum element in any subarray of size 3 or more in the input array `nums` must be greater than or equal to the value of `k`.